Melbourne w/ the fam 💛

Another beauty trip to the homeland disconnected from reality and living life outside. It’s been quite the journey. Arriving in September to an El Niño spring… (windy as). Fortunately the good weather always outweighs all the bad and a lot of the time those winds happened to be blowing the right direction. It’s been pretty fun navigating, assessing and studying the elements and hoping they all align to find those perfect places with those perfect waves. You need every little piece of the puzzle to cooperate. The swell, sand, wind and when they do, it makes you relalise why you live on the road. The last few months were spent living in the family van. A Toyota hi-ace equipped with 2 snowboard bags, 3 skateboards, 4 surfboards a bike and every other essential you need to survive day to day living. Surfing has become quite the obsession and I can not wait to keep learning the ways of the waves. Heading back to the US today. Feeling excited for the Winter ahead and grateful to be able to spend some time living like this. Cheers to my family, and everyone we bumped into and met along the way. Like I always say NZ, I’ll miss you but be right back🫶🏻
